<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-138-502  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 138 502.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACM Transactions on Programming Languages andamp; Systems  Jan 1989 v11n1 p90(25).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Distributed FIFO allocation of identical resources using smallshared space. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fischer, Michael J.; Lynch, Nancy A.; Burns, James E.; Borodin,Allan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A simple and efficient algorithm is developed for the FIFOallocation of k identical resources across asynchronous processescommunicating via shared memory.andP;  The algorithm simulates a sharedqueue but at the same time employs exponentially fewer sharedmemory values.andP;  The result is a savings not only in programcomplexity but in time and space.andP;  Robustness is achieved againstprocess failure through unannounced stopping, making the algorithmattractive also in an environment of processes of greatlydiffering speeds.andP;  In addition, for a fixed k identical resources,the algorithm's shared space complexity as a function of thenumber of processes is optimal within a constant factor.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Resource AllocationNetworksProtocolDistributed SystemsNetwork Operating SystemsReliabilityAvailabilityProcess ManagementFault ToleranceParallel ProcessingFIFOTechnologyAsynchronous ProcessesQueuesShared Memory.andO;Feature:   illustrationprogram.andO;Caption:   Queue algorithm (code for process i). (program)Basic ticket algorithm (code for process i). (program)Numbered ticket algorithm. (program)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>